{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907272739,"sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","part":{"id":"prt_d7c526b780018Cf7qENFQN3z7L","messageID":"msg_d7c5256e5001KYirHZFKI59oTR","sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n2: \n3: ## AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `sdk-python` |\n8: | **Language** | Python |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` classes as part of the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) to provide a comprehensive Python client library for interacting with the AgentCube platform. This SDK SHALL enable programmatic creation of Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execution of code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invocation of AgentRuntime workloads.\n17: \n18: The SDK SHALL:\n19: - Provide a high-level `CodeInterpreterClient` for sandboxed code execution with automatic session lifecycle management\n20: - Provide an `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking agent workloads through the Router\n21: - Support both context manager and explicit lifecycle patterns for resource cleanup\n22: - Handle authentication via Bearer tokens (environment variable or Kubernetes service account)\n23: - Implement proper connection pooling and timeout management for HTTP operations\n24: - Define a clear exception hierarchy for error handling\n25: - Support file operations (upload, download, write, list) in Code Interpreter sessions\n26: - Enable multiple programming language execution (Python, JavaScript, Bash) through the Code Interpreter\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Scope\n31: \n32: ### In Scope\n33: \n34: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient — High-Level Session Client**\n35:    - `__init__()` — Initialize with configuration for session name, namespace, TTL, and connection URLs\n36:    - `_init_data_plane()` — Initialize data plane client with session header\n37:    - `__enter__()` / `__exit__()` — Context manager support for automatic cleanup\n38:    - `stop()` — Close data plane session and delete control plane session\n39:    - `execute_command()` — Execute shell commands in the Code Interpreter sandbox\n40:    - `run_code()` — Execute code in supported languages (Python, JavaScript, Bash)\n41:    - `write_file()` — Write text content to files in the sandbox\n42:    - `upload_file()` — Upload local files to the sandbox\n43:    - `download_file()` — Download files from the sandbox to local storage\n44:    - `list_files()` — List files in the sandbox at a given path\n45: \n46: 2. **AgentRuntimeClient — Agent Workload Client**\n47:    - `__init__()` — Initialize with agent name, namespace, router URL, and timeout settings\n48:    - `__enter__()` / `__exit__()` — Context manager support\n49:    - `invoke()` — POST JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n50:    - `close()` — Explicitly close the underlying HTTP session\n51:    - Session ID bootstrapping via GET request to invocation endpoint\n52: \n53: 3. **ControlPlaneClient — Workload Manager Client**\n54:    - `create_session()` — POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` to create sessions\n55:    - `delete_session()` — DELETE session by ID with 404 handling\n56:    - `close()` — Close the HTTP session\n57:    - Environment-based URL resolution (`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n58:    - Service account token file support (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`)\n59: \n60: 4. **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — Router Client for Code Interpreter**\n61:    - `execute_command()` — POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout\n62:    - `run_code()` — Language-specific code execution (writes file then executes)\n63:    - `write_file()` — POST to `api/files` with base64-encoded content\n64:    - `upload_file()` — Multipart POST to `api/files`\n65:    - `download_file()` — GET from `api/files/{path}` with streaming\n66:    - `list_files()` — GET from `api/files` with query parameter\n67:    - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n68: \n69: 5. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — Router Client for Agent Runtime**\n70:    - `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET invocation base URL to obtain session ID\n71:    - `invoke()` — POST JSON payload with session header\n72:    - `close()` — Close HTTP session\n73:    - Timeout tuple handling `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n74: \n75: 6. **HTTP Utilities**\n76:    - `create_session()` — Factory for `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n77:    - `HTTPAdapter` configuration with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n78: \n79: 7. **Exception Hierarchy**\n80:    - `AgentCubeError` — Base exception class\n81:    - `CommandExecutionError` — Non-zero exit code with exit_code, stderr, command\n82:    - `SessionError` — Session creation/management failures (defined for extension)\n83:    - `DataPlaneError` — Data plane operation failures (defined for extension)\n84: \n85: 8. **Utility Functions**\n86:    - `read_token_from_file()` — Read and strip token file contents\n87:    - `get_logger()` — Structured logging with configurable level\n88: \n89: ### Out of Scope\n90: \n91: 1. **WebSocket Real-Time Streaming**: No WebSocket support for live output streaming (separate AR)\n92: 2. **AsyncIO Support**: Synchronous API only; async variants not included\n93: 3. **Multi-Region Load Balancing**: Single router URL per client instance\n94: 4. **Client-Side Caching**: No response caching mechanism\n95: 5. **CLI Interface**: SDK is library-only; no command-line interface\n96: 6. **TypeScript/JavaScript SDK**: Python-only implementation\n97: 7. **Custom HTTP Adapters**: Standard requests library usage only\n98: 8. **Connection Retry Logic**: Basic requests retry handling only\n99: 9. **Response Schema Validation**: JSON parsing without Pydantic models\n100: 10. **Metrics and Telemetry**: No built-in metrics collection\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## Design\n105: \n106: ### SDK Architecture\n107: \n108: ```\n109: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n110: │                    agentcube (Public API)                       │\n111: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n112: │  CodeInterpreterClient        │  AgentRuntimeClient             │\n113: │  - Session lifecycle          │  - Invoke workloads             │\n114: │  - Code execution             │  - Session bootstrap            │\n115: │  - File operations            │  - Payload posting              │\n116: └───────────────┬───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────┘\n117:                 │                               │\n118:     ┌───────────┴───────────┐       ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n119:     ▼                       ▼       ▼                       ▼\n120: ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n121: │ ControlPlane    │  │ CodeInterpreterData  │  │ AgentRuntimeData │\n122: │ Client          │  │ PlaneClient          │  │ PlaneClient      │\n123: ├─────────────────┤  ├──────────────────────┤  ├──────────────────┤\n124: │ create_session  │  │ execute_command      │  │ bootstrap_session│\n125: │ delete_session  │  │ run_code             │  │ invoke           │\n126: │ close           │  │ write_file           │  │ close            │\n127: └────────┬────────┘  │ upload_file          │  └────────┬─────────┘\n128:          │           │ download_file        │           │\n129:          │           │ list_files           │           │\n130:          │           └──────────┬───────────┘           │\n131:          │                      │                       │\n132:          └──────────────────────┼───────────────────────┘\n133:                                 │\n134:                     ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n135:                     ▼                       ▼\n136:             ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n137:             │  create_session │     │  read_token_    │\n138:             │  (HTTP utility) │     │  from_file      │\n139:             └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n143: \n144: ```\n145: __init__(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, ...)\n146:     │\n147:     ▼\n148: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n149: │ Validate router_url         │\n150: │ (arg or ROUTER_URL env)     │\n151: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n152:               │ Not provided\n153:               ▼\n154:        ┌──────────────┐\n155:        │ Raise Value  │\n156:        │ Error        │\n157:        └──────────────┘\n158:               │ Provided\n159:               ▼\n160: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n161: │ Initialize ControlPlane     │\n162: │ Client                      │\n163: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n164:               │\n165:               ▼\n166: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n167: │ session_id provided?        │\n168: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n169:               │ No\n170:               ▼\n171: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n172: │ create_session()            │\n173: │ POST /v1/code-interpreter   │\n174: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n175:               │\n176:               ▼\n177: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n178: │ _init_data_plane()          │\n179: │ (may raise)                 │\n180: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n181:               │ Raises\n182:               ▼\n183: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n184: │ Log warning                 │\n185: │ delete_session()            │\n186: │ session_id = None           │\n187: │ Re-raise                    │\n188: └─────────────────────────────┘\n189:               │ Success\n190:               ▼\n191:        ┌──────────────┐\n192:        │ Ready for    │\n193:        │ operations   │\n194:        └──────────────┘\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### AgentRuntimeClient Lifecycle\n198: \n199: ```\n200: __init__(agent_name, namespace, router_url, ...)\n201:     │\n202:     ▼\n203: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n204: │ session_id provided?        │\n205: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n206:               │ No\n207:               ▼\n208: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n209: │ GET {router}/v1/namespaces/ │\n210: │ {ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/ │\n211: │ invocations/                │\n212: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n213:               │\n214:               ▼\n215: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n216: │ Read x-agentcube-session-id │\n217: │ response header             │\n218: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n219:               │ Missing\n220:               ▼\n221:        ┌──────────────┐\n222:        │ Raise Value  │\n223:        │ Error        │\n224:        └──────────────┘\n225:               │ Present\n226:               ▼\n227:        ┌──────────────┐\n228:        │ Initialize   │\n229:        │ dp_client    │\n230:        └──────────────┘\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Class Structure\n234: \n235: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n236: \n237: ```python\n238: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n239:     def __init__(\n240:         self,\n241:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n242:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n243:         ttl: int = 3600,\n244:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n245:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n246:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n247:         verbose: bool = False,\n248:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n249:     ) -> None:\n250:         \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter client with session configuration.\"\"\"\n251: \n252:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n253:         \"\"\"Initialize data plane client with session header.\"\"\"\n254: \n255:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\": ...\n256:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n257:         \"\"\"Context manager exit - calls stop().\"\"\"\n258: \n259:     def stop(self) -> None:\n260:         \"\"\"Close data plane, delete control plane session, close HTTP sessions.\"\"\"\n261: \n262:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n263:         \"\"\"Execute shell command in sandbox; raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n264: \n265:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n266:         \"\"\"Execute code in specified language (python, javascript, bash).\"\"\"\n267: \n268:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n269:         \"\"\"Write text content to file in sandbox.\"\"\"\n270: \n271:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n272:         \"\"\"Upload local file to sandbox via multipart POST.\"\"\"\n273: \n274:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n275:         \"\"\"Download file from sandbox to local path.\"\"\"\n276: \n277:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n278:         \"\"\"List files in sandbox at given path.\"\"\"\n279: ```\n280: \n281: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n282: \n283: ```python\n284: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n285:     def __init__(\n286:         self,\n287:         agent_name: str,\n288:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n289:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n290:         verbose: bool = False,\n291:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n292:         timeout: int = 120,\n293:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n294:     ) -> None:\n295:         \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime client.\"\"\"\n296: \n297:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n298:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n299:         \"\"\"Context manager exit - calls close().\"\"\"\n300: \n301:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any:\n302:         \"\"\"POST payload to Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\"\"\"\n303: \n304:     def close(self) -> None:\n305:         \"\"\"Close underlying HTTP session.\"\"\"\n306: ```\n307: \n308: #### ControlPlaneClient\n309: \n310: ```python\n311: class ControlPlaneClient:\n312:     def __init__(\n313:         self,\n314:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n315:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n316:         timeout: int = 120,\n317:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n318:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n319:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n320:     ) -> None:\n321:         \"\"\"Initialize Workload Manager control plane client.\"\"\"\n322: \n323:     def create_session(\n324:         self,\n325:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n326:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n327:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n328:         ttl: int = 3600,\n329:     ) -> str:\n330:         \"\"\"Create session and return session_id.\"\"\"\n331: \n332:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n333:         \"\"\"Delete session; returns True (404 treated as success).\"\"\"\n334: \n335:     def close(self) -> None:\n336:         \"\"\"Close HTTP session.\"\"\"\n337: ```\n338: \n339: #### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n340: \n341: ```python\n342: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n343:     def __init__(\n344:         self,\n345:         session_id: str,\n346:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n347:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n348:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n349:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n350:         timeout: int = 120,\n351:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n352:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n353:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n354:     ) -> None:\n355:         \"\"\"Initialize data plane client for Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n356: \n357:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response:\n358:         \"\"\"Internal request with session header.\"\"\"\n359: \n360:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n361:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n362:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n363:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n364:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n365:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n366:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ### HTTP Endpoint Mapping\n370: \n371: #### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n372: \n373: | Method | Endpoint | Description |\n374: |--------|----------|-------------|\n375: | `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Create session with name, namespace, ttl, metadata |\n376: | `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | Delete session (404 = success) |\n377: \n378: **Headers:**\n379: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n380: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token resolved)\n381: \n382: #### Data Plane — Code Interpreter (Router)\n383: \n384: | Method | Endpoint | Body/Params | Description |\n385: |--------|----------|-------------|-------------|\n386: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Execute command |\n387: | `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | Write file |\n388: | `POST` | `api/files` | `files={'file': ...}, data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload file (multipart) |\n389: | `GET` | `api/files/{path}` | `stream=True` | Download file |\n390: | `GET` | `api/files` | `?path={path}` | List files |\n391: \n392: **Headers:**\n393: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (all requests)\n394: - `Content-Type: application/json` (JSON requests)\n395: \n396: #### Data Plane — Agent Runtime (Router)\n397: \n398: | Method | Endpoint | Headers | Body |\n399: |--------|----------|---------|------|\n400: | `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | — | — |\n401: | `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n402: \n403: ### Exception Hierarchy\n404: \n405: ```\n406: Exception\n407: └── AgentCubeError (agentcube.exceptions)\n408:     ├── CommandExecutionError\n409:     │   ├── exit_code: int\n410:     │   ├── stderr: str\n411:     │   └── command: Optional[str]\n412:     ├── SessionError (for extension)\n413:     └── DataPlaneError (for extension)\n414: ```\n415: \n416: ---\n417: \n418: ## Impact Analysis\n419: \n420: ### Affected Components\n421: \n422: | Component | Impact | Description |\n423: |-----------|--------|-------------|\n424: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | High | New file for CodeInterpreterClient |\n425: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High | New file for AgentRuntimeClient |\n426: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | High | New file for ControlPlaneClient |\n427: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | High | New file for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n428: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | High | New file for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n429: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Medium | Re-export client classes |\n430: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Medium | Export CodeInterpreterClient and AgentRuntimeClient |\n431: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | High | New file for exception hierarchy |\n432: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Medium | New file for create_session utility |\n433: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Low | New file for read_token_from_file |\n434: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Low | New file for get_logger |\n435: | `pyproject.toml` | Low | Package dependencies and metadata |\n436: | `examples/basic_usage.py` | Low | Example CodeInterpreterClient usage |\n437: | `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` | Low | Example AgentRuntimeClient usage |\n438: \n439: ### Package Dependencies\n440: \n441: ```toml\n442: dependencies = [\n443:     \"requests\",\n444:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n445:     \"cryptography\",\n446: ]\n447: \n448: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Configuration Resolution\n452: \n453: | Setting | Environment Variable | Default |\n454: |---------|---------------------|---------|\n455: | `router_url` | `ROUTER_URL` | Required (ValueError if missing) |\n456: | `workload_manager_url` | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `None` |\n457: | `auth_token` | Service account token file | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n458: | `timeout` | — | `120` seconds |\n459: | `connect_timeout` | — | `5.0` seconds |\n460: \n461: ### Timeout Behavior\n462: \n463: | Operation | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n464: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n465: | Control plane calls | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n466: | Data plane execute | `5.0s` | `timeout + 2.0s` (buffer) |\n467: | Data plane files | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n468: | Agent Runtime invoke | `5.0s` | `self.timeout` (default 120s) |\n469: \n470: ### Error Scenarios\n471: \n472: | Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n473: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n474: | Missing router_url | `ValueError` | Router URL must be provided |\n475: | Missing session header | `ValueError` | Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id |\n476: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Command failed (exit {code}): {stderr} |\n477: | Missing session_id for invoke | `ValueError` | AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized |\n478: | Session create without sessionId | `ValueError` | Session ID not found in response |\n479: | Data plane init failure | Warning logged, session deleted, re-raised | — |\n480: | Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (idempotent) | — |\n481: | Delete session other error | Returns `False`, logged | — |\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## Alternatives Considered\n486: \n487: ### Alternative 1: Single Client Class\n488: \n489: **Approach**: Combine CodeInterpreterClient and AgentRuntimeClient into a single unified client with mode flags.\n490: \n491: **Rejected**: Different use cases and API patterns. Code Interpreter focuses on session-based sandboxed execution with file operations, while Agent Runtime focuses on stateless payload invocation. Keeping them separate provides clearer APIs and independent evolution paths.\n492: \n493: ### Alternative 2: AsyncIO-First Design\n494: \n495: **Approach**: Build the SDK with `async`/`await` and `aiohttp` as the primary interface.\n496: \n497: **Rejected**: Adds complexity for the majority of use cases that don't need concurrent operations. The synchronous `requests`-based design is simpler and more familiar to Python developers. Async support can be added later as a separate async client module.\n498: \n499: ### Alternative 3: Pydantic Models for Validation\n500: \n501: **Approach**: Use Pydantic for request/response validation and serialization.\n502: \n503: **Rejected**: Adds a heavy dependency for relatively simple data structures. The SDK uses standard Python dictionaries and type hints, keeping dependencies minimal (requests, PyJWT, cryptography only).\n504: \n505: ### Alternative 4: Auto-Generated Client from OpenAPI\n506: \n507: **Approach**: Generate the SDK client from an OpenAPI specification using tools like openapi-generator.\n508: \n509: **Rejected**: Generated clients often have poor ergonomics and don't match the desired high-level API design. A hand-crafted client provides better control over the user experience and can handle SDK-specific concerns like session lifecycle management.\n510: \n511: ### Alternative 5: Unified Configuration Class\n512: \n513: **Approach**: Create a single `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings.\n514: \n515: **Rejected**: The distributed configuration approach is more flexible. Different clients have different configuration needs, and environment-based resolution is handled at the appropriate level. This avoids passing unnecessary configuration through multiple layers.\n516: \n517: ### Alternative 6: Retry Logic with Tenacity\n518: \n519: **Approach**: Use the `tenacity` library for sophisticated retry logic with exponential backoff.\n520: \n521: **Rejected**: Adds another dependency for functionality that `requests` handles adequately at the adapter level. Retries can be added at the application layer if needed. The SDK keeps dependencies minimal.\n522: \n523: ### Alternative 7: httpx Instead of requests\n524: \n525: **Approach**: Use `httpx` instead of `requests` for both sync and async support in one library.\n526: \n527: **Rejected**: While `httpx` is modern and supports both sync/async, `requests` is more widely used and familiar. The SDK prioritizes familiarity and stability over bleeding-edge features. Migration to `httpx` is possible in the future if needed.\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## Verification\n532: \n533: ### CodeInterpreterClient Usage Verification\n534: \n535: ```python\n536: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n537: \n538: # Context manager with automatic cleanup\n539: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n540:     name=\"my-session\",\n541:     namespace=\"default\",\n542:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n543:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n544: ) as client:\n545:     # Execute a command\n546:     output = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\", timeout=30.0)\n547:     print(output)\n548: \n549:     # Run Python code\n550:     result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"\"\"\n551: import sys\n552: print(f\"Python version: {sys.version}\")\n553:     \"\"\", timeout=60.0)\n554:     print(result)\n555: \n556:     # Write and read files\n557:     client.write_file(\"Hello, World!\", \"/tmp/hello.txt\")\n558:     client.download_file(\"/tmp/hello.txt\", \"./local_hello.txt\")\n559:     files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n560:     print(files)\n561: \n562: # Session automatically cleaned up on exit\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ### AgentRuntimeClient Usage Verification\n566: \n567: ```python\n568: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n569: \n570: # Context manager with automatic session bootstrap\n571: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n572:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n573:     namespace=\"default\",\n574:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n575: ) as client:\n576:     # Invoke the agent\n577:     response = client.invoke({\n578:         \"message\": \"Hello, Agent!\",\n579:         \"context\": {\"user_id\": \"123\"}\n580:     }, timeout=30.0)\n581:     print(response)\n582: \n583: # Session automatically closed on exit\n584: ```\n585: \n586: ### Error Handling Verification\n587: \n588: ```python\n589: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n590: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n591: \n592: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n593:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n594:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n595: ) as client:\n596:     try:\n597:         # This will raise CommandExecutionError\n598:         client.execute_command(\"exit 1\")\n599:     except CommandExecutionError as e:\n600:         print(f\"Exit code: {e.exit_code}\")\n601:         print(f\"Stderr: {e.stderr}\")\n602:         print(f\"Command: {e.command}\")\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ### Direct Client Usage Verification\n606: \n607: ```python\n608: from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n609: \n610: # Manual session management\n611: cp = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\")\n612: session_id = cp.create_session(name=\"manual-session\", namespace=\"default\")\n613: print(f\"Session: {session_id}\")\n614: \n615: # Use data plane directly\n616: dp = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n617:     session_id=session_id,\n618:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n619:     namespace=\"default\",\n620:     cr_name=\"my-interpreter\",\n621: )\n622: output = dp.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n623: print(output)\n624: \n625: # Cleanup\n626: dp.close()\n627: cp.delete_session(session_id)\n628: cp.close()\n629: ```\n630: \n631: ### Environment Configuration Verification\n632: \n633: ```python\n634: import os\n635: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n636: \n637: # Configure via environment\n638: os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = \"http://router:8080\"\n639: os.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = \"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n640: \n641: # No URL arguments needed - resolved from environment\n642: with CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"env-session\") as client:\n643:     output = client.execute_command(\"whoami\")\n644:     print(output)\n645: ```\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ## References\n650: \n651: - [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) — SDK package layout and class design\n652: - [python-sdk/spec.md](python-sdk/spec.md) — SDK requirements specification\n653: - [session-routing/design.md](session-routing/design.md) — Router API design\n654: - [sandbox-orchestration/design.md](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Workload Manager API design\n655: - [code-execution/design.md](code-execution/design.md) — Code execution service design\n656: - [requests Documentation](https://docs.python-requests.org/) — HTTP library\n657: - [Python Type Hints](https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html) — Type annotation reference\n658: - AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider (uses SDK for deployment verification)\n659: - AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (can use SDK for agent testing)\n660: - AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands (complementary functionality)\n661: \n662: ---\n663: \n664: ## Success Criteria\n665: \n666: 1. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient` class exists in `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n667: 2. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient` class exists in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n668: 3. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n669: 4. ✅ `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n670: 5. ✅ `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class exists in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n671: 6. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined in `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n672: 7. ✅ `agentcube/__init__.py` exports `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`\n673: 8. ✅ `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` re-exports all client classes\n674: 9. ✅ Context manager support (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) for both clients\n675: 10. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n676: 11. ✅ `execute_command()` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit\n677: 12. ✅ `run_code()` writes timestamped file and executes for Python code\n678: 13. ✅ File operations (`write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`) work correctly\n679: 14. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` POSTs JSON with session header\n680: 15. ✅ Session ID bootstrapping via GET request when not provided\n681: 16. ✅ Missing `router_url` raises `ValueError` with clear message\n682: 17. ✅ Missing session header in bootstrap raises `ValueError`\n683: 18. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` returns session_id from response\n684: 19. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` treats 404 as success\n685: 20. ✅ Service account token file reading works for Kubernetes environments\n686: 21. ✅ Connection pooling configured with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n687: 22. ✅ Timeout defaults: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n688: 23. ✅ `x-agentcube-session-id` header included on all data plane requests\n689: 24. ✅ Data plane init failure after session create logs warning, deletes session, re-raises\n690: \n691: ---\n692: \n693: *AR-027 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 693 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n\n## AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `sdk-python` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` classes as part of the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) to provide a comprehensive Python client library for interacting with the AgentCube platform. This SDK SHALL enable programmatic creation of Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execution of code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invocation of AgentRuntime workloads.\n\nThe SDK SHALL:\n- Provide a high-level `CodeInterpreterClient` for sandboxed code execution with automatic session lifecycle management\n- Provide an `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking agent workloads through the Router","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775907272718,"end":1775907272737}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907272745,"sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","part":{"id":"prt_d7c526f86001lmU4FVa4YBjcPU","messageID":"msg_d7c5256e5001KYirHZFKI59oTR","sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-027  \n6: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **Workload Manager API**: Control plane for session lifecycle management\n14: - **Router API**: Data plane for code execution and file operations\n15: - **Agent Runtime API**: For agent workload invocation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         User Application (Python)                            │\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐                 │\n28: │  │ CodeInterpreterClient   │    │  AgentRuntimeClient     │                 │\n29: │  │ ┌───────────────────┐   │    │ ┌───────────────────┐   │                 │\n30: │  │ │ Context Manager   │   │    │ │ Context Manager   │   │                 │\n31: │  │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │    │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │                 │\n32: │  │ └───────────────────┘   │    │ └───────────────────┘   │                 │\n33: │  └───────────┬─────────────┘    └───────────┬─────────────┘                 │\n34: │              │                              │                                │\n35: └──────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                │                              │\n37:                ▼                              ▼\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                         SDK Internal Layer                                   │\n40: │                                                                              │\n41: │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │   ControlPlaneClient        │    │       Data Plane Clients            │  │\n43: │  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │ Session Management    │  │    │  │ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient│  │  │\n45: │  │  │ · create_session()    │──┘    │  │ · execute_command()           │  │  │\n46: │  │  │ · delete_session()    │       │  │ · run_code()                  │  │  │\n47: │  │  └───────────────────────┘       │  │ · write_file()                │  │  │\n48: │  │  HTTP Session (requests)         │  │ · upload_file()               │  │  │\n49: │  │  · Connection pooling            │  │ · download_file()             │  │  │\n50: │  │  · Auth: Bearer token            │  │ · list_files()                │  │  │\n51: │  └──────────────────────────────────┘  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n52: │                                        ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n53: │                                        │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient   │  │  │\n54: │                                        │ · bootstrap_session_id()      │  │  │\n55: │                                        │ · invoke()                    │  │  │\n56: │                                        └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n57: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n58:                │                              │\n59:                ▼                              ▼\n60: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n61: │                         External Services                                    │\n62: │                                                                              │\n63: │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n64: │  │   Workload Manager          │    │         Router                      │  │\n65: │  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n66: │  │  │ POST /v1/code-        │  │    │  │ Code Interpreter Endpoints    │  │  │\n67: │  │  │         interpreter   │  │    │  │ · POST api/execute            │  │  │\n68: │  │  │ DELETE /v1/code-      │  │    │  │ · POST api/files              │  │  │\n69: │  │  │   interpreter/        │  │    │  │ · GET api/files/{path}        │  │  │\n70: │  │  │   sessions/{id}       │  │    │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n71: │  │  └───────────────────────┘  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n72: │  │  Authorization: Bearer      │    │  │ Agent Runtime Endpoints       │  │  │\n73: │  └─────────────────────────────┘    │  │ · GET /invocations/           │  │  │\n74: │                                     │  │ · POST /invocations/          │  │  │\n75: │                                     │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n76: │                                     └─────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n77: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Component Architecture\n81: \n82: ```\n83: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n84: │                     CodeInterpreterClient Flow                               │\n85: │                                                                              │\n86: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n87: │  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│  router_ │──▶│ Control  │──▶│  Create  │  │\n88: │  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │  url     │   │  Plane   │   │  Session │  │\n89: │  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │  check   │   │  Client  │   │   or     │  │\n90: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  Reuse   │  │\n91: │                                                              └────┬─────┘  │\n92: │                                                                   │        │\n93: │                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n94: │                              │                                             │\n95: │                              ▼                                             │\n96: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n97: │  │  stop()  │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│ DataPlane│◀──│ _init_   │  │\n98: │  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │  Client  │   │data_plane│  │\n99: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n100: │       │                                                           │        │\n101: │       ▼                                                           ▼        │\n102: │  ┌──────────┐                                            ┌──────────────┐  │\n103: │  │  Close   │                                            │ Execute/Files│  │\n104: │  │  Session │                                            │ Operations   │  │\n105: │  └──────────┘                                            └──────────────┘  │\n106: │                                                                              │\n107: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### AgentRuntimeClient Architecture\n111: \n112: ```\n113: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n114: │                      AgentRuntimeClient Flow                                 │\n115: │                                                                              │\n116: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n117: │  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│ router_  │──▶│ DataPlane│──▶│ Bootstrap│  │\n118: │  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │ url check│   │  Client  │   │ Session  │  │\n119: │  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │          │   │          │   │   ID     │  │\n120: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n121: │                                                                   │        │\n122: │                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n123: │                              │                                             │\n124: │                              ▼                                             │\n125: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n126: │  │  close() │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│  invoke()│◀──│  User    │  │\n127: │  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │ POST JSON│   │ Invokes  │  │\n128: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │ + Headers│   │  Agent   │  │\n129: │                                               └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n130: │                                                                              │\n131: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### Component Interactions\n135: \n136: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n137: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n138: | **CodeInterpreterClient** | High-level client for code interpreter sessions | Configuration params | Session management, code execution |\n139: | **AgentRuntimeClient** | High-level client for agent runtime invocation | Agent name, namespace, payload | Invocation response |\n140: | **ControlPlaneClient** | Workload Manager API client | Session parameters | Session ID, deletion status |\n141: | **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for code operations | Commands, files, paths | Execution results, file data |\n142: | **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for agent invocation | Payload, session ID | HTTP response |\n143: | **create_session** | HTTP session factory | Pool config | requests.Session with adapter |\n144: | **read_token_from_file** | Service account token reader | File path | Token string or empty |\n145: | **get_logger** | Logging utility | Name, level | Logger instance |\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Directory Structure\n150: \n151: ```\n152: sdk-python/\n153: ├── pyproject.toml                          # Package configuration\n154: ├── agentcube/\n155: │   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports\n156: │   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient\n157: │   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient\n158: │   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n159: │   ├── clients/\n160: │   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Client re-exports\n161: │   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient\n162: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n163: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n164: │   └── utils/\n165: │       ├── __init__.py                     # Module marker\n166: │       ├── http.py                         # create_session\n167: │       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file\n168: │       └── log.py                          # get_logger\n169: ├── examples/\n170: │   ├── basic_usage.py                      # CodeInterpreter example\n171: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py              # AgentRuntime example\n172: ├── scripts/\n173: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py                   # End-to-end test\n174: └── tests/\n175:     └── *.py                                # Unit tests\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Data Structures\n181: \n182: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n183: \n184: ```python\n185: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n186:     \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter session management and execution.\n187:     \n188:     Fields (set in __init__):\n189:         name: str                    # Session name (default: \"my-interpreter\")\n190:         namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n191:         ttl: int                     # Session TTL in seconds (default: 3600)\n192:         verbose: bool                # Enable verbose logging (default: False)\n193:         logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n194:         cp_client: ControlPlaneClient  # Control plane client\n195:         router_url: str              # Router URL (required)\n196:         session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (created or provided)\n197:         dp_client: Optional[CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient]  # Data plane client\n198:     \"\"\"\n199: ```\n200: \n201: **Constructor Parameters:**\n202: \n203: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n204: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n205: | `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Name for the code interpreter session |\n206: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n207: | `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n208: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL (or env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`) |\n209: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`, required) |\n210: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token (or service account token file) |\n211: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n212: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n213: \n214: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n215: \n216: ```python\n217: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n218:     \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n219:     \n220:     Fields (set in __init__):\n221:         agent_name: str              # Agent name\n222:         namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n223:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n224:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n225:         logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n226:         router_url: str              # Router URL (from arg or ROUTER_URL env)\n227:         session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (bootstrapped or provided)\n228:         dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  # Data plane client\n229:     \"\"\"\n230: ```\n231: \n232: **Constructor Parameters:**\n233: \n234: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n235: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n236: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Name of the agent to invoke |\n237: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n238: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`) |\n239: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n240: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n241: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Read timeout in seconds |\n242: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connect timeout in seconds |\n243: \n244: ### ControlPlaneClient\n245: \n246: ```python\n247: class ControlPlaneClient:\n248:     \"\"\"Control plane client for Workload Manager API.\n249:     \n250:     Fields:\n251:         base_url: str                # Workload Manager base URL\n252:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n253:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n254:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n255:     \"\"\"\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n259: \n260: ```python\n261: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n262:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter operations.\n263:     \n264:     Fields:\n265:         session_id: str              # Session ID for header\n266:         base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n267:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n268:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n269:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n270:     \"\"\"\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n277:     \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n278:     \n279:     Constants:\n280:         SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n281:     \n282:     Fields:\n283:         base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n284:         timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n285:         connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n286:         session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n287:     \"\"\"\n288: ```\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## API Contracts\n293: \n294: ### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n295: \n296: #### Session Creation\n297: \n298: ```\n299: POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Request:**\n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n306:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n307:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n308:   \"metadata\": {}\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: **Response:**\n313: ```json\n314: {\n315:   \"sessionId\": \"abc-123-def\"\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: **Headers:**\n320: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n321: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n322: \n323: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n324: \n325: #### Session Deletion\n326: \n327: ```\n328: DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Behavior:**\n332: - Returns `True` on success (2xx)\n333: - Returns `True` on 404 (already deleted)\n334: - Returns `False` on other errors (logs warning)\n335: \n336: ### Data Plane (Code Interpreter)\n337: \n338: #### Base URL Construction\n339: \n340: ```python\n341: if base_url is not provided:\n342:     base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n343:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n344: ```\n345: \n346: #### Execute Command\n347: \n348: ```\n349: POST {base_url}api/execute\n350: ```\n351: \n352: **Request:**\n353: ```json\n354: {\n355:   \"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"],\n356:   \"timeout\": \"60s\"\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: **Response:**\n361: ```json\n362: {\n363:   \"stdout\": \"output text\",\n364:   \"stderr\": \"error text\",\n365:   \"exit_code\": 0\n366: }\n367: ```\n368: \n369: **Timeout Behavior:**\n370: - Read timeout: `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n371: \n372: **Error Handling:**\n373: - Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n374: \n375: #### Write File\n376: \n377: ```\n378: POST {base_url}api/files\n379: ```\n380: \n381: **Request:**\n382: ```json\n383: {\n384:   \"path\": \"/workspace/script.py\",\n385:   \"content\": \"base64_encoded_content\",\n386:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Upload File (Multipart)\n391: \n392: ```\n393: POST {base_url}api/files\n394: Content-Type: multipart/form-data\n395: ```\n396: \n397: **Form Data:**\n398: - `file`: Binary file content\n399: - `path`: Remote path\n400: - `mode`: File permissions (e.g., \"0644\")\n401: \n402: **Headers:**\n403: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (only header, no JSON Content-Type)\n404: \n405: #### Download File\n406: \n407: ```\n408: GET {base_url}api/files/{clean_path}\n409: ```\n410: \n411: Where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n412: \n413: **Response:** Binary file content (streamed)\n414: \n415: #### List Files\n416: \n417: ```\n418: GET {base_url}api/files?path={path}\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Data Plane (Agent Runtime)\n422: \n423: #### Base URL Construction\n424: \n425: ```python\n426: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n427: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: #### Bootstrap Session ID\n431: \n432: ```\n433: GET {base_url}\n434: ```\n435: \n436: **Response Headers:**\n437: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (required)\n438: \n439: **Error:**\n440: - Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if header missing\n441: \n442: #### Invoke Agent\n443: \n444: ```\n445: POST {base_url}\n446: ```\n447: \n448: **Headers:**\n449: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n450: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n451: \n452: **Request Body:** JSON payload (dict)\n453: \n454: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## Error Handling\n459: \n460: ### Exception Hierarchy\n461: \n462: ```\n463: AgentCubeError (base)\n464: ├── CommandExecutionError\n465: ├── SessionError\n466: └── DataPlaneError\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### Exception Definitions\n470: \n471: ```python\n472: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n473:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n474:     pass\n475: \n476: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n477:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command returns non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n478:     \n479:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n480:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n481:         self.stderr = stderr\n482:         self.command = command\n483:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n484: \n485: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n486:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\n487:     \n488:     Defined for extension; core client modules primarily use ValueError\n489:     or requests exceptions for session-related errors.\n490:     \"\"\"\n491:     pass\n492: \n493: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n494:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\n495:     \n496:     Defined for extension; core client modules may raise ValueError\n497:     or requests exceptions for data plane errors.\n498:     \"\"\"\n499:     pass\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ### Error Scenarios\n503: \n504: | Scenario | Error Type | Message/Behavior |\n505: |----------|------------|------------------|\n506: | Router URL not provided | `ValueError` | \"Router URL must be provided\" |\n507: | Session creation fails | `ValueError` / logs | Missing `sessionId` in response |\n508: | Data plane init fails after session create | Warning log + cleanup | Deletes session, re-raises |\n509: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Includes exit_code, stderr, command |\n510: | Missing session header | `ValueError` | \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n511: | Invoke without session | `ValueError` | \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n512: | Session not found (404) | Handled gracefully | Returns `True` from `delete_session` |\n513: \n514: ### Context Manager Cleanup\n515: \n516: **CodeInterpreterClient:**\n517: ```python\n518: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n519:     \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit (success or exception).\"\"\"\n520:     self.stop()\n521: \n522: def stop(self) -> None:\n523:     \"\"\"Stop the client: close data plane, delete session, close control plane.\"\"\"\n524:     # 1. Close data plane client\n525:     # 2. Delete control plane session (if session_id was created)\n526:     # 3. Close control plane HTTP session\n527: ```\n528: \n529: **AgentRuntimeClient:**\n530: ```python\n531: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n532:     \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit.\"\"\"\n533:     self.close()\n534: \n535: def close(self) -> None:\n536:     \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Configuration Resolution\n542: \n543: ### No Centralized Configuration Class\n544: \n545: The SDK uses distributed configuration resolution across components:\n546: \n547: | Component | Setting | Resolution Order |\n548: |-----------|---------|------------------|\n549: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n550: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` file |\n551: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n552: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n553: \n554: ### Default Timeouts\n555: \n556: | Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n557: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n558: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n559: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n560: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n561: \n562: ### HTTP Connection Pool\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: defaults = {\n566:     \"pool_connections\": 10,\n567:     \"pool_maxsize\": 10,\n568: }\n569: ```\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Testing Strategy\n574: \n575: ### Test Levels\n576: \n577: | Level | Scope | Focus |\n578: |-------|-------|-------|\n579: | **Unit** | Individual classes/methods | Logic, error paths, edge cases |\n580: | **Integration** | Client + Mock Server | HTTP contract verification |\n581: | **E2E** | Full stack (optional) | Real service connectivity |\n582: \n583: ### Unit Test Coverage\n584: \n585: #### CodeInterpreterClient Tests\n586: \n587: ```python\n588: # test_code_interpreter.py\n589: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n590:     def test_init_requires_router_url(self):\n591:         \"\"\"Router URL must be provided via arg or ROUTER_URL env.\"\"\"\n592:         \n593:     def test_init_creates_session_when_not_provided(self):\n594:         \"\"\"Should create session via ControlPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n595:         \n596:     def test_init_reuses_provided_session_id(self):\n597:         \"\"\"Should not create new session when session_id provided.\"\"\"\n598:         \n599:     def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self):\n600:         \"\"\"Should delete session if data plane init fails after create.\"\"\"\n601:         \n602:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self):\n603:         \"\"\"Should call stop() on context exit.\"\"\"\n604:         \n605:     def test_execute_command_delegates_to_data_plane(self):\n606:         \"\"\"Should delegate to CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n607:         \n608:     def test_run_code_python_path(self):\n609:         \"\"\"Should write file and execute python3 for python/py/python3.\"\"\"\n610: ```\n611: \n612: #### AgentRuntimeClient Tests\n613: \n614: ```python\n615: # test_agent_runtime.py\n616: class TestAgentRuntimeClient:\n617:     def test_bootstrap_session_id_on_init(self):\n618:         \"\"\"Should GET base URL and extract session header.\"\"\"\n619:         \n620:     def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self):\n621:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session header missing.\"\"\"\n622:         \n623:     def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n624:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session_id is falsy.\"\"\"\n625:         \n626:     def test_invoke_posts_json_with_headers(self):\n627:         \"\"\"Should POST JSON with session header.\"\"\"\n628:         \n629:     def test_context_manager_closes_session(self):\n630:         \"\"\"Should close HTTP session on context exit.\"\"\"\n631: ```\n632: \n633: #### ControlPlaneClient Tests\n634: \n635: ```python\n636: # test_control_plane.py\n637: class TestControlPlaneClient:\n638:     def test_create_session_posts_json(self):\n639:         \"\"\"Should POST to /v1/code-interpreter with correct body.\"\"\"\n640:         \n641:     def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self):\n642:         \"\"\"Should return sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n643:         \n644:     def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self):\n645:         \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if response missing sessionId.\"\"\"\n646:         \n647:     def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_success(self):\n648:         \"\"\"Should return True on 2xx.\"\"\"\n649:         \n650:     def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_404(self):\n651:         \"\"\"Should return True on 404 (already deleted).\"\"\"\n652:         \n653:     def test_delete_session_returns_false_on_error(self):\n654:         \"\"\"Should return False and log warning on other errors.\"\"\"\n655:         \n656:     def test_auth_from_service_account_token(self):\n657:         \"\"\"Should read token from SA file when auth_token not provided.\"\"\"\n658: ```\n659: \n660: #### Data Plane Client Tests\n661: \n662: ```python\n663: # test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n664: class TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n665:     def test_base_url_construction(self):\n666:         \"\"\"Should construct base URL from router_url + namespace + cr_name.\"\"\"\n667:         \n668:     def test_execute_command_posts_json(self):\n669:         \"\"\"Should POST to api/execute with command array and timeout.\"\"\"\n670:         \n671:     def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self):\n672:         \"\"\"Read timeout should be timeout + 2.0 seconds.\"\"\"\n673:         \n674:     def test_execute_command_raises_on_nonzero_exit(self):\n675:         \"\"\"Should raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit_code.\"\"\"\n676:         \n677:     def test_write_file_posts_base64(self):\n678:         \"\"\"Should POST to api/files with base64 content, path, mode.\"\"\"\n679:         \n680:     def test_upload_file_multipart(self):\n681:         \"\"\"Should POST multipart with file, path, mode, session header.\"\"\"\n682:         \n683:     def test_download_file_streams(self):\n684:         \"\"\"Should GET with stream=True for file download.\"\"\"\n685:         \n686:     def test_list_files_gets_with_path_query(self):\n687:         \"\"\"Should GET api/files with path query param.\"\"\"\n688: ```\n689: \n690: ### Mock Server Integration Tests\n691: \n692: ```python\n693: # Integration test example\n694: @pytest.fixture\n695: def mock_router():\n696:     \"\"\"Start mock Router server for testing.\"\"\"\n697:     # Using responses or httpserver library\n698:     \n699: def test_full_lifecycle(mock_router):\n700:     \"\"\"Test create session, execute, stop flow.\"\"\"\n701:     with CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=mock_router.url) as client:\n702:         result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n703:         assert result == \"hello\\n\"\n704:     # Verify session deleted on exit\n705: ```\n706: \n707: ### E2E Test Script\n708: \n709: ```python\n710: # scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n711: \"\"\"End-to-end test for PicoD integration.\n712: \n713: Requires:\n714:     - Running Workload Manager\n715:     - Running Router\n716:     - Accessible Code Interpreter environment\n717: \n718: Usage:\n719:     python scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n720: \"\"\"\n721: ```\n722: \n723: ---\n724: \n725: ## Dependencies\n726: \n727: ### Required\n728: \n729: ```toml\n730: [project]\n731: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n732: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n733: dependencies = [\n734:     \"requests\",\n735:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n736:     \"cryptography\",\n737: ]\n738: \n739: [build-system]\n740: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n741: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n742: ```\n743: \n744: ### Package Discovery\n745: \n746: ```toml\n747: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n748: where = [\".\"]\n749: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n750: namespaces = false\n751: ```\n752: \n753: ---\n754: \n755: ## Public API Surface\n756: \n757: ### Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n758: \n759: ```python\n760: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n761: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n762: \n763: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n764: ```\n765: \n766: ### Clients Subpackage (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n767: \n768: ```python\n769: __all__ = [\n770:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n771:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n772:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n773: ]\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ---\n777: \n778: ## Implementation Notes\n779: \n780: ### Session Header Management\n781: \n782: - Header name: `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase)\n783: - Set as default on data plane HTTP session\n784: - Explicitly set on multipart uploads\n785: \n786: ### Timeout Handling\n787: \n788: - Control plane: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n789: - Data plane execute: `timeout + 2.0` buffer to prevent race with PicoD\n790: - Per-call override supported via method `timeout` parameter\n791: \n792: ### Python Code Execution Path\n793: \n794: When `run_code()` called with `language` in `(\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\")`:\n795: \n796: 1. Generate timestamped filename: `{name}_{timestamp}.py`\n797: 2. Write code via `write_file()`\n798: 3. Execute via `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")`\n799: \n800: ### Token Authentication\n801: \n802: 1. If `auth_token` provided, use it\n803: 2. Else try read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n804: 3. If token non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header\n\n(End of file - total 804 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Workload Manager API**: Control plane for session lifecycle management\n- **Router API**: Data plane for code execution and file operations\n- **Agent Runtime API**: For agent workload invocation\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775907272722,"end":1775907272742}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907272750,"sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","part":{"id":"prt_d7c5273c7001OhbbQZvdI0XoGG","messageID":"msg_d7c5256e5001KYirHZFKI59oTR","sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n10: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n13: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n14: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n15: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n18: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n19: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n20: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n23: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n24: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n26: \n27: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n28: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n31: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n32: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n33: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n36: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n37: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n38: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n41: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Context manager\n44: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n45: - **WHEN** the block exits\n46: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n49: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n50: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n54: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n55: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n56: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n59: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Create session\n62: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n63: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n64: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Delete session\n67: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n68: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n69: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n72: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n73: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n74: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n77: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Execute command\n80: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n81: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Files API\n84: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n86: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n90: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n93: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n95: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: Session header management\n98: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n101: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n102: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n103: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n106: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Command failure\n109: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n110: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n111: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n114: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n115: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n116: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n117: \n118: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n119: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n122: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n123: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n124: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n127: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n128: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n129: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/spec.md","time":{"start":1775907272724,"end":1775907272746}}}}
