{"type":"text","timestamp":1775907285112,"sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","part":{"id":"prt_d7c52a23d001XqYNttjsFASQpQ","messageID":"msg_d7c5278650017aw2da5jhLntkC","sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the context. The user wants me to write a `proposal.md` for **AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端**, based on the design.md and spec.md provided in the prompt file. This is different from the existing AR-027 proposal.\n\nLet me create the proposal.md:","time":{"start":1775907285110,"end":1775907285110}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907501280,"sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","part":{"id":"prt_d7c52a879001ozxrEHs9GXuLTl","messageID":"msg_d7c5278650017aw2da5jhLntkC","sessionID":"ses_283add0daffeXnLlAzhiHku2PX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: SDK HTTP Low-Level Client (AR-029)\n\n## AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `sdk-python` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the HTTP low-level client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) to provide robust, reusable HTTP communication primitives for both control plane (Workload Manager) and data plane (Router) operations. This module SHALL serve as the foundational HTTP infrastructure supporting higher-level SDK clients.\n\nThe HTTP client layer SHALL:\n- Provide a factory function `create_session()` for configuring `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n- Support configurable connection pool settings (`pool_connections`, `pool_maxsize`)\n- Enable service account token file reading for Kubernetes authentication\n- Provide structured logging utilities for SDK-wide use\n- Define a clear exception hierarchy for SDK error handling\n- Serve as the HTTP transport foundation for `ControlPlaneClient` and data plane clients\n- Support proper timeout configuration (connect and read timeouts)\n- Handle Bearer token authentication for Workload Manager API calls\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **HTTP Session Factory (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)**\n   - `create_session()` — Factory for creating `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n   - `HTTPAdapter` configuration for `http://` and `https://`\n   - Default pool settings: `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n2. **Authentication Utilities (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)**\n   - `read_token_from_file()` — Read and strip token file contents\n   - Returns empty string on `FileNotFoundError`\n   - Used for Kubernetes service account token reading\n\n3. **Logging Utilities (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)**\n   - `get_logger()` — Create structured logger with configurable level\n   - Supports standard Python logging levels\n\n4. **Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)**\n   - `AgentCubeError` — Base exception class for SDK\n   - `CommandExecutionError` — Non-zero exit code with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n   - `SessionError` — Session creation/management failures (defined for extension)\n   - `DataPlaneError` — Data plane operation failures (defined for extension)\n\n5. **HTTP Client Contracts — Control Plane (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)**\n   - `ControlPlaneClient` — Workload Manager HTTP client\n   - `create_session()` — POST `/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body\n   - `delete_session()` — DELETE session by ID with 404 handling\n   - Environment-based URL resolution (`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n   - Bearer token authentication (argument or service account file)\n   - Connection timeout: `5.0s`, Read timeout: `120s`\n\n6. **HTTP Client Contracts — Data Plane: Code Interpreter (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)**\n   - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` — Router client for Code Interpreter\n   - Base URL construction: `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n   - Session header management: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n   - `execute_command()` — POST `api/execute` with JSON body\n   - `write_file()` — POST `api/files` with base64 content\n   - `upload_file()` — Multipart POST `api/files`\n   - `download_file()` — GET `api/files/{path}` with streaming\n   - `list_files()` — GET `api/files` with query param\n   - Timeout buffer: `timeout + 2.0s` for execute command\n\n7. **HTTP Client Contracts — Data Plane: Agent Runtime (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)**\n   - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` — Router client for Agent Runtime\n   - Base URL construction: `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n   - `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` class constant\n   - `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET base URL, extract session header\n   - `invoke()` — POST JSON payload with session header\n   - Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n\n8. **Client Re-exports (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)**\n   - Re-export all client classes for internal SDK use\n\n9. **Package Configuration**\n   - `pyproject.toml` dependencies: `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`\n   - Python version requirement: `>=3.10`\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **High-Level Client Classes**: `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` (implemented in AR-027)\n2. **WebSocket Support**: Real-time streaming via WebSocket (separate AR)\n3. **AsyncIO Implementation**: `aiohttp` or `httpx` async support\n4. **Automatic Retry Logic**: Exponential backoff and circuit breaker patterns\n5. **Response Caching**: HTTP response cache layer\n6. **Metrics and Telemetry**: Request/response metrics collection\n7. **Custom SSL Configuration**: Advanced TLS/SSL settings\n8. **Proxy Configuration**: HTTP proxy support\n9. **Request/Response Validation**: Pydantic or JSON Schema validation\n10. **Rate Limiting**: Client-side rate limiting\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### HTTP Client Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           SDK HTTP Layer                                     │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │                        HTTP Utilities                                │    │\n│  │  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │    │\n│  │  │ create_session│  │ read_token_   │  │      get_logger           │ │    │\n│  │  │ (http.py)     │  │ from_file     │  │      (log.py)             │ │    │\n│  │  │               │  │ (utils.py)    │  │                           │ │    │\n│  │  │ · HTTPAdapter │  │               │  │ · Structured logging      │ │    │\n│  │  │ · Pool config │  │ · SA token    │  │ · Configurable level      │ │    │\n│  │  └───────┬───────┘  └───────────────┘  └───────────────────────────┘ │    │\n│  │          │                                                          │    │\n│  └──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│             │                                                                │\n│             ▼                                                                │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │                     HTTP Client Classes                              │    │\n│  │                                                                      │    │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n│  │  │   ControlPlaneClient    │    │        Data Plane Clients       │  │    │\n│  │  │  ┌───────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │ create_session()  │  │    │  │CodeInterpreterDataPlane   │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │ · POST /v1/code-  │──┘    │  │Client                     │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │   interpreter     │       │  │ · execute_command()       │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │ · Auth: Bearer    │       │  │ · write_file()            │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  └───────────────────┘       │  │ · upload_file()           │  │  │    │\n│  │  │                              │  │ · download_file()         │  │  │    │\n│  │  │ ┌───────────────────┐        │  │ · list_files()            │  │  │    │\n│  │  │ │ delete_session()  │        │  └───────────────────────────┘  │  │    │\n│  │  │ │ · DELETE /sessions│        │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │  │    │\n│  │  │ │ · 404 = success   │        │  │AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient│  │  │    │\n│  │  │ └───────────────────┘        │  │ · bootstrap_session_id()  │  │  │    │\n│  │  │                              │  │ · invoke()                │  │  │    │\n│  │  │ · Timeout: 120s read         │  └───────────────────────────┘  │  │    │\n│  │  │ · Connect: 5.0s              │                                   │  │    │\n│  │  │ · Pool: 10/10                │                                   │  │    │\n│  │  └──────────────────────────────┘                                   │  │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          External Services                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   Workload Manager          │    │         Router                      │  │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ POST /v1/code-        │  │    │  │ Code Interpreter Endpoints    │  │  │\n│  │  │         interpreter   │  │    │  │ · POST api/execute            │  │  │\n│  │  │ DELETE /v1/code-      │  │    │  │ · POST api/files              │  │  │\n│  │  │   interpreter/        │  │    │  │ · GET api/files/{path}        │  │  │\n│  │  │   sessions/{id}       │  │    │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  │  └───────────────────────┘  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  Authorization: Bearer      │    │  │ Agent Runtime Endpoints       │  │  │\n│  └─────────────────────────────┘    │  │ · GET /invocations/           │  │  │\n│                                     │  │ · POST /invocations/          │  │  │\n│                                     │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│                                     └─────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### ControlPlaneClient HTTP Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│   User      │────▶│   ControlPlaneClient    │────▶│   requests.Session      │\n│   Code      │     │   ┌─────────────────┐   │     │   · HTTPAdapter         │\n│             │     │   │ Resolve base_url│   │     │   · Pool 10/10          │\n│             │     │   │ · workload_     │   │     │   · Timeout 5.0/120s    │\n│             │     │   │   manager_url   │   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   └─────────────────┘   │     │                         │\n│             │     │            │            │     │                         │\n│             │     │   ┌─────────────────┐   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   │ Resolve auth    │   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   │ · auth_token OR │   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   │ · SA token file │   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   └─────────────────┘   │     │                         │\n│             │     │            │            │     │                         │\n│             │     │   ┌─────────────────┐   │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│   │ create_session()│───┼────▶│──▶ POST /v1/code-       │\n│             │     │   │ · POST JSON     │   │     │    interpreter          │\n│             │     │   │ · Return        │   │     │   Body: name, ns, ttl   │\n│             │◀────│   │   sessionId     │◀──┼─────│◀─ Response: sessionId   │\n│             │     │   └─────────────────┘   │     │                         │\n│             │     │                         │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│   ┌─────────────────┐   │     │                         │\n│             │     │   │ delete_session()│───┼────▶│──▶ DELETE /sessions/id  │\n│             │     │   │ · DELETE        │   │     │                         │\n│             │◀────│   │ · 404 = True    │◀──┼─────│◀─ 404/200 = success    │\n│             │     │   └─────────────────┘   │     │   other = False         │\n└─────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient HTTP Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│  High-Level │────▶│ CodeInterpreterDataPlane│────▶│   requests.Session      │\n│   Client    │     │       Client            │     │                         │\n│             │     │  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ Construct base_url│  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ urljoin(router,   │  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │   base_path)      │  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │     │           │             │     │                         │\n│             │     │  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ Set session header│  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ x-agentcube-      │  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ session-id        │  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │     │           │             │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ execute_command() │──┼────▶│──▶ POST api/execute     │\n│             │     │  │ · command array   │  │     │   Body: command,timeout │\n│             │◀────│  │ · timeout buffer  │◀─┼─────│◀─ Response: exit_code   │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ write_file()      │──┼────▶│──▶ POST api/files       │\n│             │     │  │ · base64 content  │  │     │   Body: path,content    │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ upload_file()     │──┼────▶│──▶ POST api/files       │\n│             │     │  │ · multipart/form  │  │     │   Multipart: file,path  │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ download_file()   │──┼────▶│──▶ GET api/files/path   │\n│             │◀────│  │ · stream=True     │◀─┼─────│◀─ Stream response       │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n└─────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient HTTP Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐\n│  High-Level │────▶│ AgentRuntimeDataPlane   │────▶│   requests.Session      │\n│   Client    │     │       Client            │     │                         │\n│             │     │                         │     │                         │\n│             │     │  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  │ bootstrap_session_│──┼────▶│──▶ GET /invocations/    │\n│             │     │  │ id()              │  │     │                         │\n│             │◀────│  │ · Read response   │◀─┼─────│◀─ Header: x-agentcube-  │\n│             │     │  │   header          │  │     │    session-id           │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n│             │     │           │             │     │                         │\n│             │────▶│  ┌───────────────────┐  │     │                         │\n│             │     │  │ invoke()          │──┼────▶│──▶ POST /invocations/   │\n│             │     │  │ · POST JSON       │  │     │   Headers: session-id   │\n│             │◀────│  │ · timeout tuple   │◀─┼─────│◀─ JSON payload          │\n│             │     │  └───────────────────┘  │     │                         │\n└─────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘     └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Class Structure\n\n#### HTTP Session Factory\n\n```python\n# agentcube/utils/http.py\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create requests.Session with connection pooling.\n    \n    Mounts HTTPAdapter for http:// and https://.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n#### Token Reader Utility\n\n```python\n# agentcube/utils/utils.py\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read and strip token file contents.\n    \n    Returns file contents stripped, or \"\" on FileNotFoundError.\n    Used for Kubernetes service account token reading.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n#### Logging Utility\n\n```python\n# agentcube/utils/log.py\ndef get_logger(\n    name: str,\n    level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO\n) -> logging.Logger:\n    \"\"\"Create structured logger with configurable level.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient\n\n```python\n# agentcube/clients/control_plane.py\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"HTTP client for Workload Manager control plane API.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize control plane client.\n        \n        - base_url: workload_manager_url or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n        - auth_token: provided OR read from /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"POST /v1/code-interpreter, return sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n    \n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"DELETE session. Returns True on success or 404.\"\"\"\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\n# agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"HTTP client for Code Interpreter data plane (Router).\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize data plane client.\n        \n        - base_url: constructed from router_url+namespace+cr_name OR provided directly\n        - session_id: used for x-agentcube-session-id header\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def _request(\n        self,\n        method: str,\n        endpoint: str,\n        body: Optional[bytes] = None,\n        **kwargs\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Internal request with session header.\"\"\"\n    \n    def execute_command(\n        self,\n        command: Union[str, List[str]],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"POST api/execute with command array and timeout.\n        \n        Read timeout: timeout + 2.0 seconds buffer.\n        Raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"POST api/files with base64 content, path, mode 0644.\"\"\"\n    \n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"POST multipart api/files with file, path, mode.\"\"\"\n    \n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"GET api/files/{path} with stream=True.\"\"\"\n    \n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"GET api/files with path query param.\"\"\"\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\n# agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"HTTP client for Agent Runtime data plane (Router).\"\"\"\n    \n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime data plane client.\n        \n        - base_url: constructed from router_url+namespace+agent_name\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"GET base_url, return x-agentcube-session-id header.\n        \n        Raises ValueError if header missing.\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"POST JSON to base_url with session header.\n        \n        Timeout: (connect_timeout, timeout).\n        \"\"\"\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### HTTP Endpoint Mapping\n\n#### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Headers | Body | Response |\n|--------|----------|---------|------|----------|\n| `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `Content-Type: application/json`<br>`Authorization: Bearer {token}` | `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` | `{\"sessionId\":\"...\"}` |\n| `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | `Authorization: Bearer {token}` | — | 2xx/404 = True, other = False |\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` = `(5.0s, 120s)`\n\n#### Data Plane — Code Interpreter (Router)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Headers | Body/Params | Description |\n|--------|----------|---------|-------------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | `{\"command\":[...],\"timeout\":\"<n>s\"}` | Execute command |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | `x-agentcube-session-id`<br>`Content-Type: application/json` | `{\"path\",\"content\"(base64),\"mode\":\"0644\"}` | Write file |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | `x-agentcube-session-id`<br>`Content-Type: multipart/form-data` | `file`, `path`, `mode` | Upload file |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{path}` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | `stream=True` | Download file |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | `?path={path}` | List files |\n\n**Base URL Construction:**\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n**Timeout:** Read timeout for execute is `timeout + 2.0s` buffer\n\n#### Data Plane — Agent Runtime (Router)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Headers | Body | Description |\n|--------|----------|---------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | — | — | Bootstrap session ID |\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | `x-agentcube-session-id`<br>`Content-Type: application/json` | JSON payload | Invoke agent |\n\n**Base URL Construction:**\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` = `(5.0s, 120s)`\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n└── AgentCubeError (agentcube.exceptions)\n    ├── CommandExecutionError\n    │   ├── exit_code: int\n    │   ├── stderr: str\n    │   └── command: Optional[str]\n    ├── SessionError (for extension)\n    └── DataPlaneError (for extension)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | High | New file: HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Medium | New file: Token file reading utility |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Low | New file: Logging utility |\n| `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Low | New file: Module marker |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | High | New file: Exception hierarchy |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | High | New file: ControlPlaneClient HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | High | New file: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | High | New file: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Medium | New file: Client re-exports |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Low | Package dependencies and metadata |\n\n### Package Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-sdk\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\".\"]\ninclude = [\"agentcube*\"]\nnamespaces = false\n```\n\n### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n|---------|------------------|---------|\n| `workload_manager_url` | arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env | `None` |\n| `auth_token` | arg → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` file | Empty string |\n| `router_url` | arg → `ROUTER_URL` env | Required for data plane |\n| `timeout` | — | `120` seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | — | `5.0` seconds |\n| `pool_connections` | — | `10` |\n| `pool_maxsize` | — | `10` |\n\n### Timeout Behavior\n\n| Client | Operation | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n|--------|-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | All | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | execute_command | `5.0s` | `timeout + 2.0s` |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | Other | `5.0s` | `120s` |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | invoke | `5.0s` | `self.timeout` (default 120s) |\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Message/Behavior |\n|----------|-----------|------------------|\n| Token file not found | Handled | Returns empty string |\n| Session create missing sessionId | `ValueError` | Session ID not found in response |\n| Delete session 404 | Returns `True` | Idempotent delete |\n| Delete session other error | Returns `False` | Logs warning |\n| Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Command failed (exit {code}): {stderr} |\n| Missing session header (Agent Runtime) | `ValueError` | Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id |\n| Bootstrap missing header | `ValueError` | Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: httpx Instead of requests\n\n**Approach**: Use `httpx` as the HTTP client library for both sync and potential future async support.\n\n**Rejected**: While `httpx` is modern and supports both sync/async, `requests` is more widely used and familiar in the Python ecosystem. The SDK prioritizes familiarity and stability. Migration to `httpx` is possible in the future if async support becomes a requirement.\n\n### Alternative 2: Centralized HTTP Client Class\n\n**Approach**: Create a single `HTTPClient` class that handles all HTTP operations for both control plane and data plane.\n\n**Rejected**: Different clients have different requirements (authentication, headers, base URL construction). A single class would become complex with conditional logic. Separate clients provide clearer separation of concerns and independent evolution paths.\n\n### Alternative 3: requests.Session Subclass\n\n**Approach**: Subclass `requests.Session` to add SDK-specific functionality.\n\n**Rejected**: Subclassing `Session` could lead to unexpected behavior with internal requests mechanisms. Composition (wrapping Session) provides better control and avoids potential conflicts with future requests updates.\n\n### Alternative 4: Pydantic for Request/Response Models\n\n**Approach**: Use Pydantic models for type-safe request/response handling.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds a heavy dependency for relatively simple data structures. The SDK uses standard Python dictionaries and type hints, keeping dependencies minimal (requests, PyJWT, cryptography only).\n\n### Alternative 5: Auto-Generated Client from OpenAPI\n\n**Approach**: Generate HTTP client code from an OpenAPI specification.\n\n**Rejected**: Generated clients often have poor ergonomics and don't match the desired SDK-specific patterns (session lifecycle, header management). Hand-crafted clients provide better control over the API design.\n\n### Alternative 6: Retry Logic with Tenacity\n\n**Approach**: Use the `tenacity` library for sophisticated retry logic.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds another dependency for functionality that may not be needed at the SDK layer. Applications can add their own retry logic using the SDK. Keeps dependencies minimal.\n\n### Alternative 7: Connection Pool Singleton\n\n**Approach**: Share a single connection pool across all SDK clients via a singleton.\n\n**Rejected**: Different clients may have different lifecycle requirements. Separate sessions allow independent cleanup and prevent one client's issues from affecting others.\n\n### Alternative 8: Async-First Design\n\n**Approach**: Build the HTTP layer with `async`/`await` from the start.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds complexity for the majority of use cases. The synchronous design is simpler and more familiar. Async support can be added later as a separate module if needed.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### HTTP Session Factory Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.utils.http import create_session\n\n# Create session with default pool settings\nsession = create_session()\nassert session.adapters[\"http://\"].config[\"pool_connections\"] == 10\nassert session.adapters[\"https://\"].config[\"pool_maxsize\"] == 10\n\n# Create session with custom pool settings\nsession = create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)\nassert session.adapters[\"http://\"].config[\"pool_connections\"] == 20\n```\n\n### Token File Reading Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.utils.utils import read_token_from_file\nimport tempfile\nimport os\n\n# Read existing file\nwith tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode='w', delete=False) as f:\n    f.write(\"my-token\\n\")\n    temp_path = f.name\n\ntoken = read_token_from_file(temp_path)\nassert token == \"my-token\"\nos.unlink(temp_path)\n\n# Non-existent file returns empty string\ntoken = read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/path\")\nassert token == \"\"\n```\n\n### Logger Utility Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.utils.log import get_logger\nimport logging\n\n# Create logger with default level\nlogger = get_logger(\"test\")\nassert logger.level == logging.INFO\n\n# Create logger with custom level\nlogger = get_logger(\"test\", level=logging.DEBUG)\nassert logger.level == logging.DEBUG\n```\n\n### Exception Hierarchy Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import (\n    AgentCubeError,\n    CommandExecutionError,\n    SessionError,\n    DataPlaneError,\n)\n\n# Verify inheritance\nassert issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError)\nassert issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError)\nassert issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError)\n\n# CommandExecutionError attributes\ntry:\n    raise CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    assert e.exit_code == 1\n    assert e.stderr == \"error\"\n    assert e.command == \"ls\"\n    assert \"Command failed (exit 1): error\" in str(e)\n```\n\n### ControlPlaneClient Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient\n\n# Initialize with URL\nclient = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n\n# Create session\nsession_id = client.create_session(\n    name=\"test-session\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    ttl=3600\n)\nassert isinstance(session_id, str)\n\n# Delete session\nresult = client.delete_session(session_id)\nassert result is True\n\n# Cleanup\nclient.close()\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.clients import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n# Initialize\nclient = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n    session_id=\"abc-123\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    cr_name=\"my-interpreter\",\n)\n\n# Base URL constructed\nassert client.base_url.endswith(\"/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\")\n\n# Execute command (requires running router)\n# output = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\", timeout=30.0)\n\n# Cleanup\nclient.close()\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n# Initialize\nclient = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n)\n\n# Base URL constructed\nassert client.base_url.endswith(\"/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\")\n\n# Cleanup\nclient.close()\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) — SDK package layout and class design\n- [python-sdk/spec.md](python-sdk/spec.md) — SDK requirements specification\n- [session-routing/design.md](session-routing/design.md) — Router API design\n- [sandbox-orchestration/design.md](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Workload Manager API design\n- [requests Documentation](https://docs.python-requests.org/) — HTTP library\n- [Python Type Hints](https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html) — Type annotation reference\n- AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient (uses this HTTP layer)\n- AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `create_session()` exists in `agentcube/utils/http.py` with connection pooling\n2. ✅ `read_token_from_file()` exists in `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n3. ✅ `get_logger()` exists in `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n4. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined in `agentcube/exceptions.py` with `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n5. ✅ `ControlPlaneClient` class exists with `create_session()`, `delete_session()`, `close()` methods\n6. ✅ `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` class exists with HTTP methods for Code Interpreter operations\n7. ✅ `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class exists with `bootstrap_session_id()` and `invoke()` methods\n8. ✅ `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` re-exports all client classes\n9. ✅ HTTP adapters configured with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n10. ✅ Default timeouts: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n11. ✅ Bearer token authentication from argument or service account file\n12. ✅ `x-agentcube-session-id` header managed on data plane requests\n13. ✅ Base URL constructed via `urljoin()` with correct path patterns\n14. ✅ `CommandExecutionError` raised on non-zero exit code\n15. ✅ Timeout buffer `+ 2.0s` for execute command to prevent race with PicoD\n16. ✅ `delete_session()` treats 404 as success (idempotent)\n17. ✅ `pyproject.toml` configured with dependencies: `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`\n18. ✅ Python version requirement: `>=3.10`\n\n---\n\n*AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775907501057,"end":1775907501274}}}}
